      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "International law, specifically the UN Convention on the Law of the Sea (UNCLOS), is the framework, but China's expansive \"nine-dash line\" claim is widely considered invalid under that framework. While China asserts historical rights, these claims are not recognized by the majority of the international community, including rulings from international tribunals. Therefore, the legal consensus leans heavily against the sweeping nature of China's territorial assertions.",
